Moorgen Wireless Smart Home offers the most comprehensive voice-controlled smart home experience with Alexa. You can enjoy hands-free control of your home lighting and other devices. Moorgen Wireless Smart Home will follow any commands you say.

Here’s a step-by-step guide:
(1)Download our “Moorgen Wireless” app on Google Play or IOS App Store;
(2)Launch the app and register a new account (or log in if you’ve already registered);
(3)Choose “Me” –＞ “The Third-Party Service” –＞ “Amazon” to get the random code;
(4)Turn on Moorgen devices and connect them to the “Moorgen Wireless” app;
(5)IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices in Moorgen Wireless app. If you rename a smart lamp as “Living Room Light”, Echo will get the name after discovering it. 
(6)Download Amazon “Alexa” app from Amazon Market, Google Play, or IOS App Store and connect Echo with the “Alexa” app;
(7)Search the Alexa Skills Directory for “Moorgen Wireless”;
(8)Choose “Devices” in the Alexa app and pull to the bottom to click “Your Smart Home Skills” and enter the skill list interface;
(9)Click “Search” to look for skills and click “Enable to Use” after choosing one skill. Enter the bound random code in the new interface. Click “Confirm” before binding succeeds.
(10)Discover devices after binding according to the hints and return to “Devices” after success. Then, you can see all your devices.
(11)Now, all setup is done. Try to speak to Echo to control your devices.

Moorgen Wireless is a complete set of smart home solution systems, including lights, motors, AC, sensors, multimedia, etc.

By linking with Alexa, you can control all smart devices using voice commands. You can ask Alexa to turn on the lights, turn off the TV, or execute a scene that can turn on all devices in your home. 

You can also create routines on your Amazon Echo so that you can have several commands performed at one time. For example, when you wake up in the morning, you can have Alexa turn on the lights, read you the daily headlines, and start the coffee pot by simply saying "Alexa, good morning."
